olive oil
1 packet gnocchi
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
½ tbs brown sugar
20 g butter
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 pear
1 cucumber
1 bag salad leaves
½ packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 tin chopped tomatoes
1 pinch chilli flakes

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. In a large baking dish, add the
gnocchi and enough olive oil to coat the gnocchi. Season and bake until
slightly crispy, 10-14 minutes.

When the gnocchi is cooked, add the chopped tomatoes, garlic & herb
seasoning, vegetable stock powder, a pinch of chilli flakes (if using), the
brown sugar and butter to the baking dish. Season and stir to combine.
Sprinkle with the shredded Cheddar cheese and bake until golden,
8-10 minutes.

While the gnocchi is baking, thinly slice the pear and cucumber. In a medium
bowl, add the cucumber, pear, spinach & rocket mix and balsamic & olive
oil dressing (see ingredients). Season and toss to coat.

Divide the garlic and herb gnocchi tray bake between bowls. Serve with the
pear salad.